								<div class="title" id="post-title-3838029">
																		Another WWS GoI Format! Woot!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163363" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;" >DarkStuff</a></span> <span class="odate time_1529177357 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Jun 2018 19:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3838029">
									

<p>Alright, before I say anything, my verdict is an upvote. However, I have some likes and dislikes, as follows:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Some&nbsp;Likes&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Dislikes</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Or&nbsp;What&nbsp;Some&nbsp;Would&nbsp;Call&nbsp;A&nbsp;Normal&nbsp;Critique</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Let's start with things I liked.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Our experts (yes, we've got some) [&#8230;]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Liked this line. Liked calling the SCP Foundation the Supervisors, seeing as I have had them call them that and some other writers for WWS have not picked up on it (not that I can complain, it's a GoI and people can do whatever they want with them, just saying I like seeing my terminology used).</p>
<p>The tone of the article is just about on point for WWS. I like that their undying kindness towards animals extends even to insects (as I had pictured them), and while I think that it would be a little weird for WWS to have <em>too</em> many greenhouses, it makes sense that they would have a few, so I enjoyed that detail. Gave insight into what their HQ and getup looks like.</p>
<p>Now, things that I didn't like. Don't worry, you did nothing <em>terrible</em>, seeing as I upvoted, but there were enough things that I felt I should make a short little list.</p>
<p>I think it's a bit weird to imply that Tim Wilson writes all the Critter Profiles. You would imagine that WWS would have a lot of them, and Tim Wilson is the head of the organization, ambassador to the SCP Foundation, manages their assets, puts on fundraisers, brings everyone coffee&#8230; you know, he has plenty of jobs. It's kind of odd to think he'd be in charge of writing Critter Profiles. It would be like implying that The Administrator writes all the SCPs. I feel the Administrator just wouldn't have time, with all the shit they need to be doing.</p>
<p>The mention of his name also feels a little forced. &quot;I, Tim Wilson&#8230;&quot; Like you just wanted to point out that you're using the character. There are other established WWS characters throughout the articles, and it'd be fine if you made some up. I just think this use of Tim Wilson as a character doesn't make total sense to me.</p>
<p>The effects of this little dude seem pretty clearly destructive, and it's a bug. I'm wondering why it's not Keter in the eyes of the Supervisors (which would put it under SCP jurisdiction)? It rides the line, so I suppose it could be Euclid, but it's tottering between the two classifications. I might mention some heavier than normal supervision by the Supervisors, to address this point? Not sure exactly when you would mention that, but I feel that it is important enough to be addressed.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Alright, and that was that. Good locusts of the apocalypse. Good critter profile. I approve&#8230; Not that you need my approval to write WWS, or that my opinion on this matters more than anyone else's, just, y'know. I like it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
